# NOTICE

## Third-Party Attributions

This project builds upon and extends concepts from the following sources:

### Microsoft DevBlogs Tutorial
**Title**: Build a RAG application with LangChain and local LLMs powered by Ollama  
**Source**: https://devblogs.microsoft.com/cosmosdb/build-a-rag-application-with-langchain-and-local-llms-powered-by-ollama/  
**Copyright**: Microsoft Corporation  
**License**: Content published under Microsoft Terms of Use

**What we adapted**:
- Core RAG architecture pattern (retrieval-augmented generation)
- LangChain + Ollama + Cosmos DB integration approach
- Vector search implementation concepts
- Document chunking and embedding strategies

**Our enhancements**:
- Added FAISS implementation as lightweight alternative
- Fixed Windows Docker Desktop networking issues (IP_ADDRESS_OVERRIDE)
- Created comprehensive documentation (5 markdown files)
- Organized code into clean project structure (simple/ vs cosmosdb/)
- Enhanced error handling and configuration management
- Added interactive chat features (history, clear commands)

### Open Source Dependencies

All Python package dependencies are listed in `requirements.txt`. Key components:

